early ppl used standard partition but now we use LVM
sudo yum install -y lvm2 -> install it
pvcreate /dev/nvme1n1
pvs
vgcreate myvg /dev/sdb
vgs
lvcreate -L +8g -n mylv myvg
lvs
mkfs.ext4 /dev/myvg/mylv
blkid
mkdir /app1
mount -t ext4 /dev/myvg/mylv /app1
df -hT /app1
ls -l /app1
echo "hi welcome to lvm" > /app1/lvm.data
ls -l /app1
cat /app1/lvm.data
now add new disk to extend lvm
pvcreate /dev/nvme2n1
vgextend myvg /dev/sdc
lvextend -L +5G -n /dev/myvg/mylv -r

umount /app1
lvremove /dev/myvg/mylv
vgremove myvg
pvremove /dev/sdb
pvremove /dev/sdc

verify by pvs vgs lvs

if want to do permanent mounting so this
vi /etc/fstab
/dev/myvg/mylv /app1 ext4 defaults 0 0
init 6 
restart terminal again can login, verify by lsblk
dynamically we can increase the size bt cannot reduce so in prod always increase it time to time 
